            <h1 id="overview">ATC-Drone SDK</h1>
            <p>Connect your drone to the Control Center for real-time tracking, conflict detection, and automated
                traffic management.</p>

            <div class="callout info">
                <strong>ATC Server URL:</strong> <code class="code-inline">http://localhost:3000</code><br>
                Make sure the ATC server is running before connecting your drone.
            </div>

            <h2 id="quickstart">Quick Start</h2>
            <p>Get your drone connected in 5 minutes:</p>

            <h3>1. Add the SDK to your project</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre># Add to your Cargo.toml
[dependencies]
atc-sdk = { path = "../atc-drone/crates/atc-sdk" }
tokio = { version = "1.0", features = ["full"] }</pre>
            </div>

            <h3>2. Connect and send telemetry</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>use atc_sdk::AtcClient;

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    // Connect to ATC server
    let client = AtcClient::new("http://localhost:3000");
    
    // Register your drone
    client.register(None).await?;
    println!("Drone registered: {}", client.drone_id().unwrap());
    
    // Send position updates
    loop {
        client.send_position(
            33.6846,    // latitude
            -117.8265,  // longitude
            50.0,       // altitude (meters)
            90.0,       // heading (degrees)
            10.0        // speed (m/s)
        ).await?;
        
        tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(1)).await;
    }
}</pre>
            </div>

            <h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>

            <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Rust 1.70+ (for SDK)</li>
                <li>ATC Server running on localhost:3000</li>
                <li>Network access between drone and server</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Clone the Repository</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>git clone https://github.com/your-org/atc-drone.git
cd atc-drone
cargo build --release</pre>
            </div>

            <h3>Run the ATC Server</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>cargo run -p atc-server --release</pre>
            </div>

            <h2 id="client">AtcClient</h2>
            <p>The main client for communicating with the ATC server.</p>

            <h3>Creating a Client</h3>
            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>use atc_sdk::AtcClient;

// Create client with default server URL
let client = AtcClient::new("http://localhost:3000");

// With custom timeout
let client = AtcClient::with_timeout("http://localhost:3000", Duration::from_secs(5));</pre>
            </div>

            <h2 id="registration">Registration</h2>
            <p>Before sending telemetry, drones must register with the ATC server.</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>// Register with auto-generated ID
let drone_id = client.register(None).await?;

// Register with custom ID
let drone_id = client.register(Some("my-drone-001")).await?;

// Register with owner (for user-specific tracking)
client.register_with_owner(Some("my-drone"), Some("username")).await?;</pre>
            </div>

            <h2 id="telemetry">Telemetry</h2>
            <p>Send position updates to the ATC server for tracking and conflict detection.</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>// Basic position update
client.send_position(lat, lon, altitude_m, heading_deg, speed_mps).await?;

// With owner tracking (for user-specific drone visibility)
client.send_position_with_owner(
    lat, lon, altitude_m, heading_deg, speed_mps,
    Some("username".to_string())
).await?;</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="callout warning">
                <strong>Update Frequency:</strong> Send telemetry at least once per second for accurate conflict
                detection.
                Drones that don't send updates for 10 seconds are marked as "Lost".
            </div>

            <h2 id="commands">Commands</h2>
            <p>Drones can poll for and respond to commands from the Control Center.</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>// Poll for pending commands
let commands = client.get_commands().await?;

for cmd in commands {
    match cmd.command_type.as_str() {
        "HOLD" => {
            // Hover in place for cmd.duration_s seconds
            println!("HOLD command received");
        }
        "RESUME" => {
            // Continue normal operation
            println!("RESUME command received");
        }
        "LAND" => {
            // Emergency landing
            println!("LAND command received");
        }
        "ALTITUDE" => {
            // Change altitude to cmd.target_altitude_m
            println!("Change altitude to {}m", cmd.target_altitude_m);
        }
        _ => {}
    }
    
    // Acknowledge command
    client.ack_command(&cmd.id).await?;
}</pre>
            </div>

